trend_summary: For two decades the area shifted from scattered woodland estates to a consolidated suburb: industrial campus enlarged eastward, infill housing filled curving cul-de-sacs, new interchange improved access, while secondary roads and parking proliferated. Despite growth, vegetation reclaimed unused clearings, keeping overall medium-density, green suburban character.
notable_changes: Progressive expansion of the eastern industrial/commercial complex with additional large roofs and parking lots.
Construction of a grade-separated highway interchange improving regional connectivity.
Infill residential development along existing curvilinear street networks, reducing vacant lots.
Creation or enlargement of storm-water ponds and landscaped water features in the southwest and central areas.
Net gain in tree canopy on former cleared sites and along roadway buffers.
